getOntology

public OWLOntologyImpl getOntology()
Specified by:
getOntology in interface OWLEntity
Returns:
The ontology attached to this OWL entity. Every OWL entity instance has a ontology attached. Usually, this ontology is the model in which it was created, i.e., the model that was subject to be queried when this instance was created. Note that "instance" here refers to the Java object instance. As such, it should not be mixed up with the term individual in the OWL terminology (or resource in RDF) because multiple ontologies may "talk about" the same OWL individual (resource), hence, it may be part of multiple ontologies.

getLabel

public java.lang.String getLabel(java.lang.String lang)
Description copied from interface: OWLEntity
Get the rdfs:label for this resource. This function will look for labels with different language codes according to the parameter. If there is more than one such resource, an arbitrary selection is made.

Specified by:
getLabel in interface OWLEntity
Parameters:
lang - The language attribute for the desired label (EN, FR, etc) or null for don't care. Will attempt to retrieve the most specific label matching the given language.
Returns:
A label string matching the given language, or null if there is no matching label, i.e., if the label for the given language does not exist return null even if a label is found for another language.

toPrettyString

public java.lang.String toPrettyString()
Description copied from interface: OWLEntity
Get a (more or less) user-friendly string representation of this entity. The following ordered procedure is used to create the string:
  1. getLabel(null). If this returns null then
  2. check if this entity is anonymous and return its anon identifier, otherwise
  3. return the short form of this' entities URI using the QName provider of the backing KB (see also QNameProvider.shortForm(URI).

Specified by:
toPrettyString in interface OWLEntity
Returns:
A "pretty" string representation.

rename

public OWLEntityImpl<?> rename(java.net.URI newURI)
Description copied from interface: OWLEntity
Rename this entity throughout the entire KB to which it "belongs". This method supports making named entities anonymous and vice versa. However, one should not rename a named entity to the same name nor does it make sense to make a anonymous entity again anonymous.

ATTENTION! One should continue working with the renamed/returned Java object rather than with the Java object instance on which this method was invoked!

Specified by:
rename in interface OWLEntity
Parameters:
newURI - The new identifier for this entity or null to make it a anonymous entity.
Returns:
The renamed entity, which may be another Java object instance!
